      "writtenOn": "2015-10-28T01:07:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Are you sure you can use standard library functions in this function, which is called in the context of a signal handler?\n\nFrom the Breakpad wiki [1]:\n\nNote: You should do as little work as possible in the callback function. Your application is in an unsafe state. It may not be safe to allocate memory or call functions from other shared libraries. The safest thing to do is fork and exec a new process to do any work you need to do. If you must do some work in the callback, the Breakpad source contains some simple reimplementations of libc functions, to avoid calling directly into libc, as well as a header file for making Linux system calls (in src/third_party/lss) to avoid calling into other shared libraries.\n\n[1] https://code.google.com/p/google-breakpad/wiki/LinuxStarterGuide",
      "revId": "9663ba241da7bbd936d132e32aa8d238752f2425",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
